# TextGenBackend (infrastructure)

Platform abstraction for the LLM inference runtime, plus the supporting value/component types. Not an
ECS system — driven by TextGenSystem (ADR 0009, 0010).

## TextGenBackend
Abstract interface: `LoadModel(modelPath, gpuLayers)` loads the session-resident GGUF model once
(offloading `gpuLayers` transformer layers to the GPU), `IsLoaded()` reports readiness,
`Generate(params)` runs one prompt→completion loop synchronously (on a worker thread) and returns the
text (empty on failure). `Create()` selects the concrete backend by the renderer-API switch, mirroring
AudioDevice / DiffusionBackend:
- **LlamaCppBackend** (DirectX11 builds) — wraps llama.cpp on the **GPU** (CUDA): it offloads the
  configured number of transformer layers (`n_gpu_layers`, from the Text Gen GPU Layers config; default
  999 = all) so generation runs at GPU speed, sharing VRAM with the renderer / diffusion backend
  (ADR 0010). Setting the config to 0 keeps it CPU-only (the pre-ADR-0010 behaviour). Compiled active
  only when PigeonLib is built with `-DPG_ENABLE_TEXTGEN=ON` (which builds llama.cpp's isolated ggml with
  `GGML_CUDA=ON` and defines `PG_LLAMA_ENABLED`); otherwise it is an inert no-op so a plain build links
  without the heavy runtime. Applies the GGUF's own chat template (system + user message).
- **TestingTextGenBackend** (Testing builds) — deterministic mock: records the loaded path + GPU-layer
  count and the last job params, returns a fixed completion echoing the prompt (`"[mock] " + prompt`).
  Lets tests exercise the full request → generate → publish path (and the config → LoadModel GPU-offload
  plumbing) with no llama.cpp, model files, or real inference.

## TextGenParams
The fully-resolved inputs of one generation handed to the backend: prompt, optional system prompt, max
tokens, temperature, top-p, and seed. Carries no ECS or resource-map knowledge.

## TextGenBackendSingletonComponent
Holds the session backend (`m_Backend`) and `m_LoadAttempted` (guards the one-time resident load).

## TextGenJob / TextGenJobSingletonComponent
TextGenJob is the in-flight (or just-finished) generation: an atomic state (pending/running/done/failed),
the target text UUID, the result string, and the worker thread (joined on destruction).
TextGenJobSingletonComponent owns the single active job via shared_ptr (null when idle); only one
generation runs at a time.

## TextGenResultSingletonComponent
The live store of finished completions (target UUID → string), written solely by TextGenSystem. The app
reads it by the target UUID to display the Generated Text. Text is not routed through the resource map
the way a Generated Texture is, because it is not a renderer resource.

## GenerateTextRequestOneFrameComponent
App-emitted (engine-typed) request: target text UUID (caller-assigned, like an audio Voice Handle),
prompt, optional system prompt, seed, and optional Text Generation Config overrides (max tokens,
temperature, top-p). Unset (≤ 0) config fields fall back to the engine defaults.
